                <head>2. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>The first Conference of Independent African States met at Accra, April 15–22. The
                    text of a message of April 14 from Secretary of State <persName
                        corresp="#p_DJF1">Dulles</persName> to Prime Minister <persName
                        corresp="#p_NK2">Kwame Nkrumah</persName>, extending best wishes for the
                    conference, and the text of the joint declaration issued at Accra on April 22
                    are printed in <hi rend="italic">American Foreign Policy: Current Documents,
                        1958, pages 1074–1075.</hi> Documentation relating to the conference is in
                    Department of State, Central File 770.00.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
